<p>We dropped DirecTV a few years ago because of the expense and the annoyance of having to sort through hundreds of channels of garbage, trying to find something worth watching, while often not succeeding. There are a <em>few</em> shows we watch, and I am willing to pay for the content I want to see. Right now we buy about four TV series on iTunes to watch whenever we want, commercial free.</p>
